WEBVTT

00:01.793 --> 00:03.170
Good morning, DiMeos.

00:03.170 --> 00:04.922
Mysterious.
You have my interest.

00:04.922 --> 00:06.465
These are
the Channel Islands.

00:06.465 --> 00:09.009
There are eight of them ‐‐
Santa Cruz, Anacapa ‐‐

00:09.009 --> 00:11.345
‐You lost my interest.
‐Oh, no, let him finish, Jimmy.

00:11.345 --> 00:13.347
Go on about the map, darling.
Where's the treasure?

00:13.347 --> 00:16.099
My class is taking a trip
to the Channel Islands.

00:16.099 --> 00:19.895
A week of peace and relaxation
I desperately need.

00:19.895 --> 00:21.939
A Ray‐cation, if you will.

00:21.939 --> 00:23.273
‐That's clever.
‐Thanks.

00:23.273 --> 00:25.067
Not write‐it‐on‐your‐hand
clever.

00:25.067 --> 00:26.276
[ Laughs ]

00:26.276 --> 00:27.903
There's one problem.

00:27.903 --> 00:29.780
The boat leaves at 8:00 a. m.
sharp, no exceptions.

00:29.780 --> 00:31.114
So, my question.

00:31.114 --> 00:33.534
Can we please,
for once in our lives,

00:33.534 --> 00:34.952
be on time for something?

00:34.952 --> 00:37.162
Tomorrow?
No, I need more time than that.

00:37.162 --> 00:38.830
The field trip
is in a month.
Oh.

00:38.830 --> 00:40.582
If we wait a month, someone else
could find the treasure.

00:40.582 --> 00:42.167
Do you know what?
I'm offended.

00:42.167 --> 00:44.795
I mean, of course we'll get you
to your field trip on time.

00:44.795 --> 00:46.672
Don't worry.
‐Thank you.

00:46.672 --> 00:49.466
And if we're a few minutes late,
big deal, they'll wait.

00:49.466 --> 00:51.593
No, we have to be on time.

00:51.593 --> 00:53.095
I want practice runs.

00:53.095 --> 00:55.097
With enough preparation,
we can do this.

00:55.097 --> 00:57.474
Okay,
we'll do practice runs.

00:57.474 --> 00:59.518
Geez, Ray, we're not even late
that often.

00:59.518 --> 01:00.644
We're late for school
right now.

01:00.644 --> 01:02.771
Yeah, he wrote that
on his hand, too.

01:02.771 --> 01:04.606
See, that's my kind
of presentation.

01:04.606 --> 01:08.026
♪♪

01:12.030 --> 01:14.700
♪♪

01:14.700 --> 01:16.243
Let's go, people!

01:16.243 --> 01:18.203
We need to take
these practice runs seriously

01:18.203 --> 01:19.913
if I'm gonna get
to my field trip on time.

01:19.913 --> 01:22.416
‐How much time do we have?
‐Three minutes.

01:22.416 --> 01:23.500
Gotcha.
Just gonna take a quick bath.

01:23.500 --> 01:24.960
No baths!

01:24.960 --> 01:27.087
Mom, you said you'd be out here
ten minutes ago!

01:27.087 --> 01:29.047
I'm getting JJ dressed,
okay?

01:29.047 --> 01:30.841
JJ's right here!

01:30.841 --> 01:32.759
Okay, fine.
I was doing a maze.

01:32.759 --> 01:35.012
The monkey found the bananas.

01:35.012 --> 01:36.680
Finally!
Three down, two to go.

01:36.680 --> 01:37.806
I forgot
my sack of marbles.

01:37.806 --> 01:39.641
Are you from The Depression?

01:39.641 --> 01:41.768
Okay, Dad,
can we just go now?

01:41.768 --> 01:43.645
Hey, whole family
has to do practice runs,

01:43.645 --> 01:45.272
'cause we all want to
see you off for your trip.

01:45.272 --> 01:47.858
Okay, now we're just
waiting on Mom.

01:47.858 --> 01:49.109
Mom!

01:50.569 --> 01:51.778
And the boat left.

01:52.779 --> 01:54.156
I give us a B‐plus.

01:55.032 --> 01:57.034
[ School bell rings ]

01:57.034 --> 01:59.494
Dude, there's Claire.

01:59.494 --> 02:01.246
You asked her out
over a week ago.

02:01.246 --> 02:03.040
When are you gonna set up
that date?

02:03.040 --> 02:06.460
"She was
just being nice."

02:06.460 --> 02:08.795
Would you stop with that?
I'm telling you that ‐‐

02:08.795 --> 02:10.213
Hey, JJ.

02:10.213 --> 02:11.673
Don't kill me.

02:11.673 --> 02:13.634
I know we were supposed to see
"Rocky" together,

02:13.634 --> 02:15.636
but I watched it
over Thanksgiving.

02:15.636 --> 02:17.512
Sorry.

02:17.512 --> 02:20.474
Yeah, my family had it on,
and I couldn't say no.

02:20.474 --> 02:21.683
And I loved it.

02:21.683 --> 02:23.226
I am in your hands.

02:23.226 --> 02:24.853
Whatever movie you pick next,
that's what we're watching.

02:24.853 --> 02:27.147
♪♪

02:31.777 --> 02:33.570
[ Door opens ]

02:33.570 --> 02:35.155
Christmas is coming!

02:35.155 --> 02:37.199
Are we doing it?

02:37.199 --> 02:39.326
Time for my little psychic
to tell me

02:39.326 --> 02:42.412
which toy
every kid will have to have.

02:42.412 --> 02:43.872
So we can hoard them,
jack up the price,

02:43.872 --> 02:46.792
and fleece desperate schmucks
who can't tell their kids no.

02:46.792 --> 02:48.877
I'm sorry.
I just love this time of year.

02:48.877 --> 02:50.379
24 hours
with these puppies,

02:50.379 --> 02:51.963
and I'll come back
with your winner.

02:51.963 --> 02:53.674
Right there.
That's why you're my favorite.

02:53.674 --> 02:54.758
Back here, doing homework.

02:54.758 --> 02:55.592
Yeah, you are.

02:55.592 --> 02:58.345
♪♪

02:58.345 --> 03:01.056
Mr. and Mrs. DiMeo?
We have big news.

03:02.307 --> 03:04.184
"I like a girl."

03:04.184 --> 03:06.395
Good for you, Kenneth.
Go to her.

03:06.395 --> 03:07.938
JJ likes a girl.

03:07.938 --> 03:10.148
‐No! Really?
‐Hang on!

03:10.148 --> 03:11.400
Yeah, that's right.

03:11.400 --> 03:12.734
She's coming over Friday
to watch a movie.

03:12.734 --> 03:14.152
That's amazing!

03:14.152 --> 03:15.862
It is not amazing.
It is normal.

03:15.862 --> 03:17.322
Don't say "normal."
Say "typical."

03:17.322 --> 03:19.157
Son, that is typical.

03:19.157 --> 03:20.367
That doesn't feel
like anything.

03:20.367 --> 03:21.702
Tell us about her.
What's she like?

03:21.702 --> 03:23.036
Is she hot?

03:23.036 --> 03:24.621
‐She's a child!
‐Oh, fine.

03:24.621 --> 03:26.248
"She is hot."

03:26.248 --> 03:27.124
Nice.

03:27.124 --> 03:29.126
Oh, we're so excited.

03:29.126 --> 03:30.794
We knew it was
only a matter of time.

03:30.794 --> 03:32.421
Oh, it's finally happening!

03:32.421 --> 03:33.922
It's finally happening.

03:33.922 --> 03:35.841
We knew it was only
a matter of time.

03:35.841 --> 03:38.093
I don't want JJ
to get his heart broken, Jimmy.

03:38.093 --> 03:40.303
And it would take a very special
girl to be with him.

03:40.303 --> 03:41.513
And she's hot.

03:41.513 --> 03:43.181
What are the chances
she's hot <i>and</i> special?

03:43.181 --> 03:45.934
‐I mean, you are.
‐Yeah, yeah.

03:45.934 --> 03:48.395
I want to help him,
like I do with everything else.

03:48.395 --> 03:49.521
But this is different.

03:49.521 --> 03:51.398
I can't exactly yell at that
girl to make her love him.

03:52.983 --> 03:54.151
No, you can't.

03:56.027 --> 03:57.154
What if I yell
at the mother?

03:57.154 --> 03:58.196
Maya!

03:58.196 --> 04:00.615
♪♪

04:00.615 --> 04:02.117
No.

04:02.117 --> 04:03.452
[ Exhales sharply ]

04:04.870 --> 04:06.246
Ray:
You've lost your touch.

04:06.246 --> 04:08.623
You're too old to tell
which of these is fun.

04:08.623 --> 04:11.376
No. That's not the problem.
They're all fun.

04:11.376 --> 04:13.003
A dog that poops, fun.

04:13.003 --> 04:14.754
Big Top Junie?

04:14.754 --> 04:16.631
Who wouldn't want a clown doll
that laughs for no reason?

04:16.631 --> 04:19.009
[ Doll laughing ]

04:19.009 --> 04:21.136
Read the room, Junie!

04:21.136 --> 04:23.722
My powers and my childhood ‐‐
they've left me.

04:23.722 --> 04:26.725
I guess it's time to experience
the joys of womanhood.

04:26.725 --> 04:28.560
Do you know
what night "Scandal's" on?

04:28.560 --> 04:30.103
How are you gonna tell Dad?

04:30.103 --> 04:31.938
It's your special thing
with him.

04:31.938 --> 04:33.064
And that smile he gets?

04:33.064 --> 04:34.941
It's time!

04:34.941 --> 04:35.984
There it is.

04:35.984 --> 04:38.653
So?

04:38.653 --> 04:40.614
Which one's gonna be
the hot toy this year?

04:40.614 --> 04:43.992
♪♪

04:43.992 --> 04:46.870
It's her, Big Top Junie.

04:46.870 --> 04:48.205
She has won my heart.

04:49.206 --> 04:50.540
Amazing, Dylan.

04:50.540 --> 04:53.502
See, I‐I look at this,
and I think, "This is awful.

04:53.502 --> 04:55.295
No one's gonna want this."

04:55.295 --> 04:57.339
And yet, off I go
to buy a dozen.

04:57.339 --> 04:59.090
That's vision.

04:59.090 --> 05:01.843
What are you thinking?

05:01.843 --> 05:03.178
Shut up, Ray.

05:03.178 --> 05:05.055
[ Doll laughing ]
Oh, it laughs too?

05:05.055 --> 05:06.723
Aah! I hate it!

05:06.723 --> 05:09.059
Ugh!

05:09.059 --> 05:11.645
♪♪

05:11.645 --> 05:13.772
[ Humming ]

05:15.315 --> 05:16.566
We snuck in the back

05:16.566 --> 05:18.235
'cause we didn't want to
disturb JJ on his date.

05:18.235 --> 05:19.778
Aw, you're
making him a snack.

05:19.778 --> 05:21.988
Uh, no.
Oh, good idea, though.

05:21.988 --> 05:23.573
No, I'm giving him
his space.

05:23.573 --> 05:26.076
JJ can't put the moves on her
if I'm in there.

05:26.076 --> 05:27.828
Are you kidding?

05:27.828 --> 05:29.704
He can't put the moves on her
<i>unless</i> you're in there.

05:30.831 --> 05:32.415
"Citizen Kane" was good.

05:32.415 --> 05:34.209
But what did it say on the sled?
I couldn't read it.

05:37.587 --> 05:39.464
Maya: Oh, God.

05:39.464 --> 05:42.259
It's like a Richard Pryor/
Gene Wilder movie.

05:42.259 --> 05:44.052
What were you thinking?

05:44.052 --> 05:45.679
I didn't want to
crowd them.

05:45.679 --> 05:47.848
I wanted things
to progress naturally.

05:47.848 --> 05:49.599
Do you see a lot of things
progressing naturally with JJ?

05:49.599 --> 05:52.519
Does he progress naturally
from the house to the car?

05:52.519 --> 05:55.272
Does food progress naturally
to his mouth?

05:55.272 --> 05:58.275
I'm seeing your point,
but your tone is unwelcome.

05:58.275 --> 05:59.651
Listen,
you make a good sandwich,

05:59.651 --> 06:01.653
but as a wing man for JJ,
you kind of suck.

06:01.653 --> 06:03.822
Seriously though,
amazing sandwich.

06:03.822 --> 06:06.116
[ Gasps ]
I know how I can help him!

06:06.116 --> 06:07.909
All this time
I've been worried

06:07.909 --> 06:09.870
about JJ getting
his heart broken,

06:09.870 --> 06:12.455
but his biggest challenge is
simply the act of dating.

06:12.455 --> 06:14.291
It's an accessibility
issue.

06:14.291 --> 06:16.543
I can do that. I've been
doing that his whole life.

06:16.543 --> 06:19.254
JJ needs a ramp
to this girl's ‐‐
Heart.

06:19.254 --> 06:21.548
That is so sweet.
I was gonna say "boobs."

06:21.548 --> 06:23.049
Hi, darling.

06:23.049 --> 06:25.677
"Her ride's here.

06:25.677 --> 06:27.345
Get the door?"

06:27.345 --> 06:29.389
Mommy's gonna help you with
your love life, darling.

06:30.557 --> 06:32.017
"Ew."

06:34.728 --> 06:37.147
With all due respect, the night
went better than you think.

06:37.147 --> 06:39.149
JJ might be about
to get his first kiss.

06:42.485 --> 06:43.987
[ Door opens ]

06:43.987 --> 06:46.239
Later, gator.

06:46.239 --> 06:48.116
[ Door closes ]

06:49.659 --> 06:50.952
Just a little help?

06:52.662 --> 06:55.123
"Please,
please, please?"

06:55.123 --> 06:56.958
Please, please?

06:58.418 --> 06:59.252
The last two were mine.

07:03.673 --> 07:05.342
Let's go,
let's go, let's go!

07:05.342 --> 07:07.552
‐What about my breakfast?
‐No time, here!

07:07.552 --> 07:09.846
Can't find my pants.

07:09.846 --> 07:11.056
‐No time!
‐Huh?

07:11.056 --> 07:13.141
[ Tires screech ]

07:13.141 --> 07:14.517
Cut through that alley!

07:14.517 --> 07:16.853
[ Tires screech ]

07:16.853 --> 07:18.063
I feel like Vin Diesel!

07:20.190 --> 07:21.524
Ooh, JJ's trying
to say something.

07:21.524 --> 07:23.443
W‐H‐E ‐‐ "Whee!"

07:23.443 --> 07:24.986
We got this!
We got this!

07:24.986 --> 07:26.905
Ooh, that store
sells Big Top Junie.
Pull over!

07:26.905 --> 07:28.323
[ Tires screech ]

07:28.323 --> 07:29.324
Hey, watch it!

07:29.324 --> 07:30.367
[ Tires screech ]

07:33.536 --> 07:34.913
[ Sighs ]

07:34.913 --> 07:35.997
And the boat left.

07:37.248 --> 07:39.334
JJ faces some challenges

07:39.334 --> 07:41.294
in his quest to woo
this young lady.

07:41.294 --> 07:44.547
Romance blooms
in the garden of spontaneity.

07:44.547 --> 07:46.675
A perfectly timed
word of affection,

07:46.675 --> 07:48.718
a well‐timed kiss.

07:48.718 --> 07:50.220
Are you gonna be doing
all those things?

07:50.220 --> 07:51.680
Wrong!

07:51.680 --> 07:54.140
With our help, you will do
everything on your date

07:54.140 --> 07:55.767
to make this girl
fall in love with you

07:55.767 --> 07:57.143
and live
happily ever after.

07:57.143 --> 07:58.311
Now, what issues
are we facing?

07:58.311 --> 08:00.355
No hot tub, huh?

08:00.355 --> 08:02.440
I don't want to hear
why you think

08:02.440 --> 08:04.734
a hot tub is essential
to seduction, Kenneth.

08:04.734 --> 08:06.486
It's not something you <i>tell.</i>
It's something you <i>show.</i>

08:06.486 --> 08:07.612
And you ain't invited.

08:07.612 --> 08:10.532
There is positioning
that needs to happen.

08:10.532 --> 08:13.868
Initiating a kiss
is a tough nut to crack.

08:13.868 --> 08:15.620
It is not a Mummy kiss,

08:15.620 --> 08:16.996
which is so easy.

08:16.996 --> 08:18.039
Mwah!

08:18.039 --> 08:20.166
You run a weird meeting,
dear.

08:20.166 --> 08:22.043
JJ's date is going to be
like Disneyland.

08:22.043 --> 08:24.337
It will appear effortless,
but behind the scenes

08:24.337 --> 08:26.923
it will be preparation,
work, and precision.

08:26.923 --> 08:28.049
Are you in?

08:29.718 --> 08:32.053
Are you sure you don't want to
just borrow my hot tub?

08:33.388 --> 08:34.931
Ah, you're here.

08:34.931 --> 08:36.433
Sit in this.
Put this on.

08:36.433 --> 08:38.268
Your brother's
going to seduce you.

08:38.268 --> 08:40.979
Really? You're not gonna
resist that at all?

08:40.979 --> 08:42.897
‐It's nice to feel wanted.
‐Mm.

08:42.897 --> 08:44.774
JJ, your date is here.

08:44.774 --> 08:46.359
Oh, you look nice!

08:47.819 --> 08:50.947
"Thanks.
You look nice, too."

08:50.947 --> 08:53.283
Oh, confident!

08:54.701 --> 08:56.995
Ah, so she has to be
right next to you.

08:56.995 --> 08:58.413
Yes.
Stay in character.

08:58.413 --> 09:00.707
And you're watching
the movie.

09:00.707 --> 09:03.043
You had me at hello.
Claire is eating her olives.

09:03.043 --> 09:04.419
I don't like olives.

09:04.419 --> 09:05.837
Claire does.
Eat the olives.

09:05.837 --> 09:07.505
Maya: And Claire goes
to the bathroom.

09:10.216 --> 09:11.593
Pit stop!

09:11.593 --> 09:14.596
♪♪

09:17.599 --> 09:19.059
And Claire!

09:19.059 --> 09:20.685
[ Toilet flushes ]

09:20.685 --> 09:22.020
Claire!

09:24.522 --> 09:27.067
‐Dude, where were you?
‐I actually had to go.

09:27.067 --> 09:29.027
Okay,
the movie's about over.

09:29.027 --> 09:30.945
This is the time when Claire's
gonna give you that look.

09:30.945 --> 09:32.447
What look?
The look that says,

09:32.447 --> 09:34.949
"Kenneth, please take me
to your hot tub."

09:34.949 --> 09:36.826
And you know what to do when
she gives you that look, right?

09:39.621 --> 09:40.872
[ Groans ]

09:43.958 --> 09:45.126
You get the idea.

09:48.171 --> 09:50.465
‐We are go.
‐Copy.

09:50.465 --> 09:51.883
[ Airhorn sounding ]

09:51.883 --> 09:53.301
What is that?

09:58.473 --> 10:00.016
Clear.
[ Airhorn stops ]

10:00.016 --> 10:02.310
So smooth!

10:04.312 --> 10:06.314
And that is how you do it,
people!

10:06.314 --> 10:07.774
Well done.
‐Sensational.

10:07.774 --> 10:09.484
‐Nice work.
‐Yes.

10:09.484 --> 10:11.319
All that, and you can't get me
to a field trip on time?

10:11.319 --> 10:14.656
♪♪

10:14.656 --> 10:16.241
Good news.

10:16.241 --> 10:18.118
My eBay store
just opened,

10:18.118 --> 10:20.995
and the Big Top Junies
are flying off the shelves.

10:20.995 --> 10:22.330
Somebody
just bought five.

10:22.330 --> 10:24.666
‐Really? Who?
‐Astronomyguy57 something.

10:24.666 --> 10:26.000
Anyway, I got to go
ship these guys out.

10:27.836 --> 10:30.797
I'm Astronomyguy57802!

10:30.797 --> 10:32.924
You used my account
to go buy those dolls?

10:32.924 --> 10:35.969
Do you have any idea how much
that man charges for shipping?

10:35.969 --> 10:37.637
Relax.
I'll pay you back.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.347
Yeah, well how do you think
Dad's gonna feel

10:39.347 --> 10:40.682
when he finds out
his little lucky charm

10:40.682 --> 10:41.850
is pulling a fast one
on him?

10:41.850 --> 10:42.892
What do you want, Ray?

10:42.892 --> 10:45.228
Your full cooperation
on our next dry run.

10:45.228 --> 10:48.439
Done, but only because I support
you leaving for a week.

10:48.439 --> 10:49.983
Hurtful.
I'll take it.

10:49.983 --> 10:52.652
<i>‐Miss Watson...</i>
<i>‐What do you want?</i>

10:52.652 --> 10:54.946
<i>Could you come out and give me</i>
<i>a hand with EMERAC, please?</i>
<i>Look, Sumner ‐‐</i>

10:54.946 --> 10:56.656
I get my cast off soon,

10:56.656 --> 10:58.658
and then it's back to training,
training, training.

10:58.658 --> 11:01.828
Kind of wish I could put off
gymnastics for a little while.

11:03.955 --> 11:07.542
"I could break your arm."

11:07.542 --> 11:09.377
[ Laughs ]

11:09.377 --> 11:11.087
Not a lot of guys
could make that sound sweet.

11:11.087 --> 11:12.297
[ Both laugh ]

11:16.342 --> 11:18.136
Uh, is the bathroom
over there?

11:18.136 --> 11:19.846
Cool.

11:21.556 --> 11:24.142
♪♪

11:25.894 --> 11:28.563
"Do you have to watch?

11:28.563 --> 11:29.939
It's weird."

11:29.939 --> 11:30.899
No, it's not weird,
darling.

11:30.899 --> 11:32.275
It's a sensual Disneyland.

11:32.275 --> 11:33.651
Are you feeling
any vibe?

11:33.651 --> 11:35.445
Are you ready
to go for the kiss?

11:35.445 --> 11:38.615
"I can't tell.
It was easier with Ray."

11:38.615 --> 11:41.034
Not all girls
are as easy as your brother.

11:41.034 --> 11:42.493
We'll give <i>you</i> the signal

11:42.493 --> 11:44.412
when it's time
to give <i>us</i> the signal.

11:44.412 --> 11:46.164
[ Toilet flushes ]
She's coming!

11:47.415 --> 11:48.416
[ Door opens ]

11:50.835 --> 11:52.795
My mom texted.

11:52.795 --> 11:54.339
She'll be here soon.

11:54.339 --> 11:56.132
Oh, yeah,
that's the green light.

11:56.132 --> 11:57.300
What?

11:57.300 --> 11:58.760
This has been really fun.

11:58.760 --> 12:00.845
‐Is that the green light?
‐I'm not sure.

12:00.845 --> 12:02.388
My God, yes!

12:02.388 --> 12:03.723
You think everything is
the green light, hot tub man.

12:03.723 --> 12:07.852
"I had fun too."

12:07.852 --> 12:10.688
I feel like not a lot of people
get to do this.

12:10.688 --> 12:11.981
It's nice.

12:15.693 --> 12:17.820
‐The signal!
‐It's go time.

12:17.820 --> 12:20.531
[ Airhorn sounding ]

12:20.531 --> 12:22.200
What is that?

12:25.411 --> 12:26.496
Clear.
[ Airhorn stops ]

12:26.496 --> 12:28.414
That was weird.

12:38.800 --> 12:40.760
[ Cellphone chirps ]

12:40.760 --> 12:42.637
Oh, my mom's here.

12:42.637 --> 12:44.180
See you later, JJ.

12:45.640 --> 12:48.893
Yeah, huh?
Movies are fun, right?

12:50.728 --> 12:52.355
[ Door opens ]

12:52.355 --> 12:54.065
What happened?

12:54.065 --> 12:56.025
Jimmy:
"You were watching.

12:56.025 --> 12:58.945
I couldn't do it
without you.

12:58.945 --> 13:02.615
I couldn't do it
with you."

13:05.493 --> 13:09.205
Safe to say this date
was not normal or typical.

13:14.669 --> 13:16.004
How's my right, darling?

13:16.004 --> 13:17.714
All clear, honey.

13:17.714 --> 13:20.216
I can't believe it!
We're gonna make it on time.

13:20.216 --> 13:21.926
Early, even.

13:21.926 --> 13:23.303
We should stop
for breakfast.

13:23.303 --> 13:25.680
Well,
let's not get cocky.

13:25.680 --> 13:28.683
‐Breakfast sounds lovely.
‐"We've earned it."

13:28.683 --> 13:30.893
No, no, no, no, no!

13:30.893 --> 13:32.770
And the boat left.

13:32.770 --> 13:34.605
I give up.

13:34.605 --> 13:36.190
Does that mean your pancakes
are up for grabs?

13:36.190 --> 13:37.233
Yeah, good call.

13:39.235 --> 13:41.738
You promised you wouldn't
mess up the dry run!

13:41.738 --> 13:43.489
I know,
but here's the thing.

13:43.489 --> 13:44.782
I was lying.

13:44.782 --> 13:47.493
Well, if you don't want me
to tell Dad about the toy,

13:47.493 --> 13:48.911
then I have some demands.

13:48.911 --> 13:50.079
I can't live like this.

13:52.331 --> 13:55.585
Dad?
I've lost my touch.

13:55.585 --> 13:57.837
I played with the toys,
and I didn't like them.

13:57.837 --> 14:00.048
I'm too old.

14:00.048 --> 14:02.050
I'm not your
psychic little girl anymore.

14:02.050 --> 14:05.428
You <i>pretended</i>
to like Big Top Junie?

14:05.428 --> 14:06.554
Why?

14:06.554 --> 14:09.140
I wanted you
to still think I was special.

14:09.140 --> 14:12.518
You don't have to like some toy
to be special to me.

14:12.518 --> 14:14.812
You're special
just being you.

14:14.812 --> 14:17.356
That's what
parents of murderers say.
Yeah.

14:17.356 --> 14:18.483
I ruined our tradition,

14:18.483 --> 14:20.109
and I probably cost you
a lot of money

14:20.109 --> 14:22.361
with those cackling,
freakish clowns.

14:22.361 --> 14:23.738
Look, don't worry
about the money.

14:23.738 --> 14:25.698
I'm the adult.
You just relax, kiddo.

14:25.698 --> 14:27.366
You're special.

14:27.366 --> 14:30.244
You don't have to kill anybody,
but you're special.

14:30.244 --> 14:32.080
Seriously,
I was only able to find

14:32.080 --> 14:33.581
a few of those dolls
anyway.

14:33.581 --> 14:35.625
Thanks, Dad.

14:35.625 --> 14:38.419
♪♪

14:44.175 --> 14:46.636
[ Dolls laughing ]

14:49.013 --> 14:52.100
<i>This</i> is why
people save receipts.

14:53.518 --> 14:56.646
Oh! I love this!

14:56.646 --> 14:58.856
They get back together
in the end.

14:58.856 --> 15:01.025
Ah! that's why they call it
a spoiler, isn't it?

15:02.318 --> 15:03.736
Is Claire
coming back soon?

15:03.736 --> 15:05.571
No?

15:05.571 --> 15:07.949
Oh, darling.

15:07.949 --> 15:11.244
I'm sorry.
I went a bit overboard.

15:11.244 --> 15:13.162
I don't know
if you've noticed ‐‐

15:13.162 --> 15:14.163
I sometimes do that.

15:16.499 --> 15:20.336
"Hey, you helped me
score with Ray."

15:20.336 --> 15:22.421
[ Laughs ]

15:22.421 --> 15:24.423
Yeah.
I was thinking.

15:24.423 --> 15:27.552
Next time,
you should be east of the girl.

15:27.552 --> 15:30.054
That way, her lips
would be pointing west ‐‐

15:30.054 --> 15:33.349
"We tried the best version
of what <i>you'd</i> do.

15:33.349 --> 15:38.271
Next time
I'll try what <i>I'd</i> do."

15:38.271 --> 15:40.064
So, I'm just gonna
leave it to you?

15:42.108 --> 15:44.569
But that is
so hard for me.

15:45.945 --> 15:47.989
"I believe in you."

15:47.989 --> 15:50.116
[ Chuckles ]

15:53.161 --> 15:55.621
[ TV turns back on ]

15:55.621 --> 15:56.956
Oh, he dies.

15:58.291 --> 16:00.418
♪♪

16:01.669 --> 16:03.004
[ Gasps ]
Channel Islands!

16:05.715 --> 16:07.175
"Can we talk?"

16:07.175 --> 16:10.553
I kind of need to rest up
for my trip.

16:10.553 --> 16:12.263
What is it?

16:12.263 --> 16:14.140
"Claire texted me.

16:14.140 --> 16:17.727
She gets her cast off
tomorrow."

16:17.727 --> 16:19.312
Can we celebrate
in the morning?

16:19.312 --> 16:22.106
"I won't see her as much.

16:22.106 --> 16:25.735
I never told her
I like her."

16:25.735 --> 16:27.737
Wish I could tell you
what to do.

16:30.698 --> 16:31.908
"I know.

16:31.908 --> 16:35.578
I need to tell her
A‐L‐ alone.

16:35.578 --> 16:40.541
But I don't know how
to get to the hospital."

16:40.541 --> 16:43.502
I can actually help
with that.

16:43.502 --> 16:46.005
♪♪

16:48.507 --> 16:50.176
Come on.

16:50.176 --> 16:52.511
You think I'd leave the fate
of Ray‐cation in Mom's hands?

16:52.511 --> 16:55.348
I spent my life savings
on this car service.

16:55.348 --> 16:58.517
So, we'll drop you off
at the hospital where Claire is,

16:58.517 --> 17:00.061
and then I'll get to the boat
in plenty of time.

17:01.562 --> 17:04.815
"Can we stop
for breakfast?"

17:04.815 --> 17:07.068
[ Chuckles ]

17:07.068 --> 17:10.988
Ray? Ray, come on.
Let's go.

17:10.988 --> 17:12.531
Ray overslept?

17:12.531 --> 17:14.909
On the day of the big field trip
he was so worried about?

17:14.909 --> 17:17.370
[ Chuckles ] That is
some classic dramatic irony.

17:18.496 --> 17:20.456
What?
I went to college.

17:20.456 --> 17:21.749
‐Ray?
‐JJ!

17:21.749 --> 17:23.251
They left.

17:23.251 --> 17:25.628
Ray took JJ to the hospital
to profess his love to Claire.

17:25.628 --> 17:27.797
They thought
I was asleep.

17:27.797 --> 17:30.424
They always talk girls
when they think I'm asleep.

17:30.424 --> 17:32.093
The things they would do
to Emma Watson.

17:33.010 --> 17:35.054
We have to warn her.

17:35.054 --> 17:38.099
♪♪

17:38.099 --> 17:40.059
JJ!
What are you doing here?

17:41.602 --> 17:45.856
"You can go anywhere
in a hospital

17:45.856 --> 17:48.234
when you're
in a wheelchair."

17:48.234 --> 17:49.360
[ Chuckles ]

17:52.905 --> 17:53.990
Oh, is that for me?

17:53.990 --> 17:55.324
Oh.

17:57.201 --> 18:00.413
"I wanted to do this
in a more subtle way,

18:00.413 --> 18:02.456
but it turns out
I can't really do subtle.

18:02.456 --> 18:05.876
So, I am just going to
tell you how I feel.

18:07.128 --> 18:09.005
I really like you, Claire.

18:09.005 --> 18:11.132
You're smart, funny,

18:11.132 --> 18:13.884
and I hope you feel
the same way about me."

18:13.884 --> 18:16.846
Did you know the Channel Islands
have their own species of fox?

18:16.846 --> 18:17.638
Of course I knew that.

18:17.638 --> 18:19.640
Oh.

18:19.640 --> 18:20.975
Okay, we should go.

18:24.353 --> 18:26.272
Hey, how'd it go?

18:28.482 --> 18:31.444
Oh, man, I'm sorry.
Are you okay?

18:33.321 --> 18:35.740
Mr. DiMeo, we should go.

18:35.740 --> 18:37.867
[ sighs ]

18:37.867 --> 18:41.704
"You'll be late."

18:46.417 --> 18:48.544
There's been
a change of plans.

18:48.544 --> 18:50.838
Yeah, they left the hospital.
They're headed west.

18:50.838 --> 18:52.506
They must be on a bus?

18:52.506 --> 18:53.841
Where are they going?

18:53.841 --> 18:55.343
Ooh, these things don't actually
see into the future.

18:55.343 --> 18:57.011
Oh, why did
I encourage this?

18:57.011 --> 18:57.762
JJ wasn't ready.

18:57.762 --> 18:58.846
Now he's gonna get
his heart broken,

18:58.846 --> 19:00.598
and I'm not even there.

19:00.598 --> 19:04.018
Ray: And then one time,
I told a girl that I liked her,

19:04.018 --> 19:06.020
and she said, "Sorry,
but I'm not a lesbian."

19:06.020 --> 19:07.480
[ Laughs ]

19:07.480 --> 19:09.440
You don't have to laugh
that hard.

19:09.440 --> 19:11.567
It was the summer
I let Mom layer my hair.

19:11.567 --> 19:14.153
And, of course,
you know about Jillian.

19:15.488 --> 19:18.491
I know what it's like
to put yourself out there

19:18.491 --> 19:20.201
and have it not work out.

19:21.952 --> 19:24.622
"How do you get over it?"

19:24.622 --> 19:28.959
I did all I could do.
At least I have no regrets.

19:32.588 --> 19:35.800
"To no R‐E‐‐ 'regrets.'"

19:35.800 --> 19:37.468
[ Bottles clink ]

19:38.886 --> 19:40.721
You know what?

19:40.721 --> 19:42.765
High school girls just
aren't mature enough for us.

19:42.765 --> 19:44.100
Our time
will be in college.

19:45.601 --> 19:47.603
Grad school
at the latest.

19:47.603 --> 19:50.815
All right, according to this,
they are...in the ocean?

19:50.815 --> 19:52.316
‐What?
‐Sorry, near the ocean.

19:52.316 --> 19:54.276
‐No, I‐I overreacted.
‐There they are!

19:54.276 --> 19:55.736
Oh, he needs his mother.

19:55.736 --> 19:57.571
No, wait.

19:58.781 --> 20:02.034
He seems...fine.

20:02.034 --> 20:04.704
He actually looks happy.

20:04.704 --> 20:06.956
Looks like with a little help
from the people he loves,

20:06.956 --> 20:09.583
he's strong enough to handle
whatever life throws his way.

20:09.583 --> 20:11.794
What are you
even looking at?

20:11.794 --> 20:13.045
Ray and JJ are over there.

20:14.630 --> 20:17.633
Damn sun ruined my moment.

20:17.633 --> 20:19.719
Are we just gonna sit here,
or are we gonna go get 'em?

20:19.719 --> 20:22.096
Let's give them a moment.

20:22.096 --> 20:24.724
♪♪

20:24.724 --> 20:27.977
Oh, I wish I could hear
what they're saying.

20:27.977 --> 20:30.730
Damn,
Emma Watson's hot.

20:36.819 --> 20:41.073
At last, Ray‐cation.

20:41.073 --> 20:43.159
See? It's easy to mock
when you're outside the tub.

20:43.159 --> 20:46.454
But 112 degrees later,
they all believe.

20:46.454 --> 20:48.706
Oh, I believe.

20:48.706 --> 20:50.124
[ Chuckles ]

20:50.124 --> 20:52.209
You're a good brother, Ray.
You deserve it.

20:52.209 --> 20:54.336
I'll leave you to it.

20:54.336 --> 20:57.047
It's better
than I expected.

20:57.047 --> 21:00.843
I can't believe I made it out
to the Channel Islands.

21:00.843 --> 21:02.970
Okay, let's get you
out of there.

21:02.970 --> 21:05.097
Unh‐unh. Come on.
